description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re Hiring – Outpatient Pharmacists – ZERO HOUR/TEMPORARY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Relief Outpatient Pharmacist Monday to Sunday&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PLEASE NOTE THAT THIS IS FOR AD-HOC/TEMPORARY SHIFTS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;– Bold Environment and Community Spirited&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whittington Pharmacy is a vibrant state of the art workspace based in an enviable location within The Whittington Hospital, North London. Our aim is to provide the very best, efficient, safe and friendly service, tailored to the needs of our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a Community Interest Company, wholly owned by Whittington Health NHS Trust, which means that our business is designed to make a real difference to our local community. Any profits we do make are reinvested into services for Whittington Health, to help local people live longer and healthier lives by providing safe, personal, coordinated care for the community we serve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; – Experts in Medicines Supply and Advice&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The pharmacy will dispense all outpatient prescriptions for the Trust and offer a wide range of over the counter and pharmacy only medicines for sale, along with expert professional health and wellbeing advice. We will also offer a range of innovative pharmacy services which the successful applicant would be expected to help deliver and promote.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your role &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;– Work with real purpose&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a vacancy for this exciting new venture, and are looking to recruit a Pharmacist. The focus of your role will be as Responsible Pharmacist, provide support to the Superintendent Pharmacist/Managing Director and the rest of the rest of the pharmacy team. You will help in ensuring a high quality patient and customer experience is maintained, providing personalised solutions to help people lead healthier lives – this is work with real purpose.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for the provision of a range of exceptional professional pharmacy services and would be expected to help develop and drive forward services to meet the needs of our patients, staff and the local community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are we looking for &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;– Passionate people and a small high performing team &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will ideally have experience of working in a busy community or hospital pharmacy and be able to demonstrate exceptional communication and caring skills, along with confidence and the ability to question. You will be a GPhC registered pharmacist with at least two years post registration experience and will be highly motivated, passionate and able to work as part of our small high-performing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join Us &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;– Benefits and rewards to recognise you and your potential&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive salary pa pro-rata, pension, generous holiday and a performance-related bonus scheme will be offered, in addition to professional support and development. When we welcome you on board to our team we do so with the intention of helping you grow and develop your skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or an informal chat about the opportunities with Whittington Pharmacy, please contact Chirag Patel, Superintendent Pharmacist Whittington Pharmacy CIC by email chirag.patel9@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position available immediately. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that this post does not fall under NHS Agenda for Change as Whittington Pharmacy is a Community Interest Company&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chirag Patel, Superintendent Pharmacist Whittington Pharmacy CIC by email chirag.patel9@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
